Announcement has been made by Mr. and Mrs. Hildreth L. Stong of Tiburon, Calif., of the engagement of their daughter Elizabeth Snow Stong to John Shaw Cassidy, the son of Margaret S. Cassidy of South Bend, Ind., and the late John A. Cassidy.

The future bride is an associate at the New York law firm of Cravath, Swaine & Moore. She graduated magna cum laude in 1978 from Harvard University, where she was elected to Phi Beta Kappa, attended the Universite des Sciences Sociales in Toulouse, France, as a graduate fellow in public health, and received a J.D. degree from the Harvard Law School. Her father is a real-estate broker in Tiburon. Her mother, Constance S. Stong, is fiscal coordinator for the Family Service Agency of Marin in San Rafael, Calif.

Mr. Cassidy, an associate counsel in the legal department of the Federal Reserve Bank of New York, graduated magna cum laude with the class of '78 from Harvard and cum laude from the Harvard Law School. His mother is a guidance counselor with the South Bend Community School Corporation. His father was professor and chairman of the English department at Indiana University at South Bend.